TableContextTimeStampAfterTable: {17201=FRESHMAN (1998-99) - One of two freshmen to start all 19 matches and played all 1,869 minutes in goal...set WSU single season mark for most minutes in goal...collected 120 saves, placing her second on the season save list, behind Natalie McDowell (1993) with 123...made the most saves and earned the most shutouts (6) of any WSU freshman goalkeeper...ranks third in single season shutouts...shutout Eastern Washington Sept. 1 in WSU debut...kept the eventual Pac-10 Champion USC Trojans scoreless in the 2-0 upset victory Oct. 9...season high 12 saves versus Minnesota Sept. 21...shutout conference leading Washington through double overtime in the Cougs' 1-0 win to end the season...allowed just two goals in eleven overtime periods...team's Co-MVP and Co-Rookie of the Year...member of WSU All-Academic team., 24887=Lindsey Jorgensen - Freshman (1998-99), 18847=PERSONAL - Born Lindsey Jennet Jorgensen June. 30, 1980, at Butte, Mont...parents Frank and Becky...brother Josh...her uncle Chris Plager played basketball at Mankato State, while cousin Nathan ran track at Kentucky...enjoys swimming, mountain biking, hiking and basketball...her U-15 club team and U-19 club team each finished second at state...National Honor Society member (corresponding secretary...DARE role model...prep GPA of 4.0 earned numerous scholar awards...undeclared major., 16480=SOPHOMORE (1999-2000)– One of three players to start all 19 matches…played 1,684 minutes in goal, which is the second highest single season total at WSU…set WSU career shutout mark with her 11th against UC Irvine Oct. 3…led the Pac-10 with school-record 126 saves, making her just the second goalie to lead the Pac-10 in saves in consecutive seaosns…had four games with double digit saves, including 11 in the first game of the season against Boise State Sept. 4 and the last game of the season against Stanford Nov. 7…played in all but 28 minutes in goal…had back-to-back shutouts against Louisville Sept. 10 and Wyoming Sept. 12…member of the Pac-10 All-Academic first team., 36326=Lindsey Jorgensen - Sophomore (1999-00), 47619=Lindsey Jorgensen - Junior (2000-01), 15805=JUNIOR (2000-2001) – Posted best GAA of her career with 0.89 which ties for second all time…Pac-10 All-Conference second team…earned All-Far West third team honors from Soccer Buzz…Pac-10 All-Academic first team…named for a second year to the GTE/CoSIDA Academic All-America District VIII first team…named the team’s MVP and most inspirational player…posted five solo shutouts for second year…broke minutes in goal record…started 18 games missing two with a concussion mid-season…made 12 saves in double ot loss to USC, including two in final 30 seconds of regulation to force game into overtime…made 96 saves…played 1,720 minutes.}
